29 People sustained injuring when a bus overturned on the R71 in Magoebaskloof on Sunday.On arrival paramedics from ER24 and Limpopo Emergency Services found the bus lying on its side. All of the occupants were found on the side of the road and were assessed by paramedics. Majority of them sustained minor scrapes and bruises.&#8220;It is understood that they were on their way to a funeral when the incident occurred. All 29 occupants were transported to Mediclinic Tzaneen and Van Velden Provincial Hospital for further care,&#8221; said ER24 Spokesperson Werner Vermaak.The cause of the incident is not yet known.-TNA Reporter 